{"title":"Hyundai teases a three-row Ioniq 9 electric SUV","link":"https://arstechnica.com/uncategorized/2024/10/hyundai-teases-a-three-row-ioniq-9-electric-suv/","date":1730300404000,"content":"<p>In November, Hyundai will formally unveil its next electric vehicle. It's the new Ioniq 9, a three-row SUV that uses Hyundai Motor Group's highly competent E-GMP platform seen in the Ioniq 5 and <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/cars/2023/04/the-2023-hyundai-ioniq-6-a-streamlined-look-equals-serious-range/\">6</a>. Ahead of that reveal, the automaker shared some teaser images.</p>\n<p>Regular readers will know that Hyundai's various design directions always have interesting names, and like the two smaller Ioniqs, the Ioniq 9 will feature \"parametric pixels\" in its headlampsâ€”the blocky 8-bit look has been used to good effect on the Ioniq 5 and Ioniq 6.</p>\n<figure>\n    <div>\n                        <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1043\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-300x122.jpg 300w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-640x261.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-768x313.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-1536x626.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-2048x835.jpg 2048w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-980x399.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/63892-HyundaiMotorPresentsFirstLookatIONIQ9EmbarkingonaNewEraofSpaciousEVDesign-1440x587.jpg 1440w\" />\n                  </div>\n      </figure>\n\n<p>E-GMP has already given rise to a big electric three-row SUV. <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/cars/2024/01/2024-kia-ev9-first-drive-a-flawed-but-fine-family-flagship/\">Kia's EV9</a> has been on sale for a while now and has just about matched the cheaper EV6 in terms of sales for the last nine months, despite a $54,900 starting price that's more than $12,000 greater than the EV6's. (American car buyers really do want larger cars, and they vote with their wallets.)</p><p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/uncategorized/2024/10/hyundai-teases-a-three-row-ioniq-9-electric-suv/\">Read full article</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/uncategorized/2024/10/hyundai-teases-a-three-row-ioniq-9-electric-suv/#comments\">Comments</a></p>","author":"Jonathan M. Gitlin","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0ddf6e8923e49262a7894cfd77962733e43fbcc565a103b48373820b310636","entryHash":"1be70f327d228f553ecfda1d00eaa3c0ef2fb54a59a647d5bda44b0ee1bd5feb","category":"Tech"}